A '''Godcast''' is a [[podcast]] of [[religion|religious]] nature, including music, preaching, [[seminary]] lectures, [[Bible]] readings, meditations and kids' programs. Such podcasts are available within most religious traditions and across multiple formats - audio only as well as audio-visual.
The number of Godcasts is growing rapidly - many are created by independent churches, synagogues, and seminaries and materials have been recorded by [[Pope Benedict XVI]]. [http://www.cnn.com/2005/TECH/12/27/spark.godcasting]
== Etymology == The Godcast Network appears{{Where|date=July 2011}} to have been the first to register the term on the web, creating its Christian podcast site in October 2004. Founder Craig Patchett holds a trademark on the term.<ref>Patchett, Craig A. Godcast. Registration No. 3092654, United States Patent and Trademark Office, 16 May 2006.</ref>
